translated: Lars Georg, provincial doctor, Jörlanda, b. 2/8/98 in Kärrbo, Västmanland. Son of County Governor Claes W. and Charlotte Levénhaupt. Married on 26th of May to Ulla Cederström. Children: Birgitta b. 1927, Sten b. 1920, Anne-Marie b. 193a, Ulrika b. 1931, Margareta b. 1934, Cecilia b. 1940, Elisabeth b. 1942, Claes-Johan b. 1944. Education: Graduated from Västerås in 1916, Medical Degree from Uppsala in 1922, Medical License from Karolinska Institute in 1927. Assistant doctor at Nyköping Hospital in 1924, temporary provincial doctor in Bjurholm district in 1926 and 1927, assistant doctor and temporary deputy senior doctor at Karlshamn Hospital for thirteen months in 1926 and 1927, temporary provincial doctor in Fränsta and Svenljunga districts in 1927 and 1928, municipal employee in Tranemo from 1927 to 1928, temporary deputy provincial doctor in Tranemo district from 1929 to 1930, regular deputy provincial doctor from 1930, provincial doctor in Jörlanda district since 1942, railway doctor at Falkenberg Railway from 1928 to 1934. Chairman of Tranemo Health Committee from 1930 to 1934, chairman of Jörlanda Circle of Swedish Red Cross since 1943. Claes Evald Wessberg, headmaster, Trollhättan, b. 30/5/91 in Torslanda, Gothenburg and Bohuslän. Son of Edvard W. and Charlotta Tönnesdotter. Married firstly on 21st of May to Gertrud Lindqvist who died in 1927, and secondly on 31st of May to Ruth Lindqvist. Children: Claes-Henrik b. 1922, Gertrud b. 1926. Education: Graduated from Gothenburg Latin School in 1915, Bachelor of Arts from Gothenburg University in 1915, Master of Arts in 1916, student of teaching at Norra Latin in Stockholm in the spring of 1928. Temporary subject teacher in Vara municipality between 1916 and 1917, temporary subject teacher in Nässjö between 1917 and 1918, teacher at Trollhättan Coeducational School from 1918 to 1919, subject teacher at Trollhättan Municipal Intermediate School from 1919 to 1927, adjunct in mother tongue, German and history at Trollhättan Intermediate School since 1928, temporary headmaster from 1920 to 1921, headmaster of municipal intermediate school from 1921 to 1930, of intermediate school since 1930. Auditor of the church's accounts and administration from 1929 to 1931, advocate for freedom of the press since 1931, representative for oversight of certain school funds, inspector for vocational schools, member of church council. Trips to Germany in 1912, 1921, and 1937, participated in Swedish Red Cross invalid transport in 1915 and 1917. Receipient of the Royal Order of Vasa, the Royal Order of the Lion of Finland in silver. Thérèse Wessberg, dentist, Gothenburg, born in Maltnö to railway engineer and shipbuilder A.P. Wessberg and Kerstin Andreasson. Graduated from ÄMinska School in Stockholm in 1901, dental degree in 1902, registered dentist in 1904. Assistant in Hässleholm in 1904, practice in Västervik from 1905 to 1912, assistant in Falkenberg from 1912 to 1915, school dentist in Gothenburg from 1916 to 1942, had her own practice in Gothenburg since 1924. Claes Hugo Wessén, major, Halmstad, b. 26/11/96 in Veinge, Halland. Son of editor Viktor Larsson and Sigrid Wessén. Married on 21st of March to Margit Drakenberg. Children: Barbro b. 1923, Birgitta b. 1929, Gunvor b. 1934. Education: Graduated from Halmstad in 1915, military officer exam in 1917, signal training courses in 1924 and 1929. Second lieutenant of former Västergötland Regiment in 1917, lieutenant in 1919, of Halland Regiment in 1928, captain in 1932, major in the army in 1945. Mobilized officer from 1940. Secretary of Halland 1st Association from 1933 to 1937, chief instructor there from 1938 to 1940, member of its executive committee from 1935 to 1945. Recipient of the Commander Cross of the Order of the Sword, the Cross of Civilian Merit in Halland. Daniel Gotthold Johannes Wessén, lawyer, Mjölby, b. 27/10/96 in Högby, Östergötland. Son of clergyman C.G. W. and Lydia Sehman. Education: Graduated from Linköping in 1914, law degree from Uppsala in 1919, court service in Lysings, Göstrings and Mjölby districts from 1921 to 1924. Own legal practice in Mjölby since 1924. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1936. Disposition for Mjölby Canon's Residence Joint Stock Company since 1941. Member of the city council. Writings: Miscellaneous essays in legal subjects.
